tourBios.exmtStatus: 33rd Web.com Tour Qualifier at the 2009 PGA TOUR Qualifying Tournament
tourBios.carHigh: Posted a third-round, 12-under 60 during the first stage of Q-School in 2009, eventually advancing to the final stage...Missed the cut at the 2007 Stanford St. Jude Championship in his only career PGA TOUR start...Has never played on the Web.com Tour...Most recently made the cut in nine of 12 starts on the 2009 Canadian Tour, with a T10 at the Montreal Open his best finish. Has also played on the Hooters Tour in 2006-08 and the Gateway Tour in 2006.
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Winner of the 2002 Florida State Amateur Championship.
tourBios.personal: States winning the Florida State Amateur Championship, with his dad caddying, as his biggest thrill in golf...Course he'd most like to play is Pebble Beach...Never travels without a football...Favorite college team is Georgia State University and favorite professional team is the Tampa Bay Buccaneers...Favorite city to visit is Denver and favorite vacation spot is Las Vegas...Would round out his dream foursome with Michael Jordan, Charles Barkley and world poker champion Phil Ivey.
tourBios.priorYearSeason: Collected his first top-10 finish in 12 starts with a T7 at the Fort Smith Classic, thanks to weekend rounds of 66-65.

tourBios.otherInfo: Also has played on the PGA TOUR and the Hooters Tour
tourBios.prYrSeason: Had a consistent 2012 season, making his final seven cuts and posting six top-30 finishes

dyn.dynResults: His best finish on the Web.com Tour was T7th in 2010 at the Fort Smith Classic.
